Media personality Chrissy Teigen and her husband John Legend have lost their baby due to pregnancy complications. The media personality, who is the host of Lip Sync Battle, in a lengthy heart-breaking Instagram post said they are shocked and in pain following the death of their son, Jack. “We are shocked and in the kind of deep pain you only hear about, the kind of pain we’ve never felt before.” READ: MOSHE'S GOING TO BE A FATHER! The distraught media personality, who was hospitalised on Sunday night after enduring a month of bleeding due to having a weak placenta, said doctors were unable to stop the bleeding. “We were never able to stop the bleeding and give our baby the fluids he needed, despite bags and bags of blood transfusions. It just wasn’t enough.” She also thanked everyone who have been supporting them in this difficult time of their lives. “Thank you to everyone who has been sending us positive energy, thoughts and prayers. We feel all of your love and truly appreciate you,” she said. pic.twitter.com/iBFKYtYwi2 